## C# Style

Use sealed classes unless inheritance is needed.
Prefer [SerializeField] private + read-only public accessors.
Small components with one job.
Cache references in Awake/Start.
Early returns over deep nesting.
Clear warnings with object context: Debug.LogWarning("...", this);
Avoid GetComponent in Update, FindObjectOfType in gameplay, and per-frame allocations.


